                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310217-185-off1110 t18310217-185-crimeloc1113"></join>. I lost this saddle on the 3rd of February from a wooden horse at the door of my shop - the door stands in about six inches; it was market-day - I had the saddle in my possession at half-past ten o'clock, and missed it about twelve; I saw it again on the Saturday.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310217-185-person1813">
                  JAMES 
                  CHURCH
               <interp inst="t18310217-185-person1813" type="surname" value="CHURCH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-185-person1813" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-185-person1813" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a foot-patrol. I apprehended the prisoner on the Windsor road, about seven miles from Uxbridge, about half-past four o'clock, on the 3rd of February - he went into a harness-maker's shop, at Slough, and offered this saddle for sale; he said he would give me the saddle if I would let him go - as we were going back he threw down the saddle, and again said he would give it me to let him go - I took him to the Red Lion, and sent for the officer to take him.</p>
               <p>JAMES BACON. I was sent for by Mr. Church, about half-past five o'clock, to take the prisoner - this is the saddle.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
